Thoracic adhesive apparatus present, consisting of ridges of skin (striae) in elliptical field extending from isthmus to level of last pectoral-fin ray base, with lanceolate median depression on posterior half almost enclosed posteriorly by skin ridges (
Fig. 2
). Striae uninterrupted; medial striae orientated anteriorly, lateral ones anterolaterally.

Distribution. Known from the Myittha River, a tributary of the Chindwin River in western Myanmar (
Fig. 3
).
